metadata.title: Climate Models KG

metadata.title: DREAM-KG

metadata.title: SAWGraph FIO KG

metadata.title: GEOCONNEX
metadata.description: Geoconnex is an open, community-driven knowledge graph linking U.S. hydrologic features to enable seamless water data discovery, access, and collaborative monitoring.

metadata.title: SAWGraph Hydrology KG
metadata.description: The Hydrology KG is part of the SAWGraph project.

metadata.title: ID Mappings

metadata.title: NASA-GESDISC-KG
metadata.description: The NASA Knowledge Graph Dataset is an expansive graph-based dataset designed to integrate and interconnect information about satellite datasets, scientific publications, instruments, platforms, projects, data centers, and science keywords. This knowledge graph is particularly focused on datasets managed by NASA's Distributed Active Archive Centers (DAACs), which are NASA's data repositories responsible for archiving and distributing scientific data. In addition to NASA DAACs, the graph includes datasets from 184 data providers worldwide, including various government agencies and academic institutions.

metadata.title: NIAID Data Ecosystem KG
metadata.description: The nde (NIAID Data Ecosystem) KG contains infectious and immune-mediated disease datasets. These include datasets from NIAID-funded repositories as well as globally-relevant infectious and immune-mediated disease (IID) repositories from NIH and beyond. The datasets include -omics data, clinical data, epidemiological data, pathogen-host interaction data, flow cytometry, and imaging.

metadata.title: Neighborhood Information KG
metadata.description: Neighborhood Information KG (NIKG) is a knowledge graph warehouse for neighborhood information.

metadata.title: Rural Resilience KG
metadata.description: Rural Resilience KG is a cross-domain knowledge graph to integrate health and justice for rural resilience.

metadata.title: SAWGraph PFAS graph
metadata.description: The Safe Agricultural Products and Water Graph (SAWGraph) PFAS graph stores data on PFAS observations and releases, describing the samples, the geospatial features they were taken from, the sampled environmental media, the specific chemical substances and the measurement values observed.

metadata.title: SCALES
metadata.description: SCALES is an integrated justice platform to connect criminal justice data across data silos.

metadata.title: SecureChain KG
metadata.description: SecureChain is a knowledge graph for resilient, trustworthy, and secure software supply chains.

metadata.title: SemOpenAlex
metadata.description: Comprehensive information on scientific publications and related entities.

metadata.title: SOC-KG
metadata.description: The Soil Organic Carbon Knowledge Graph (SOCKG) enhances robust soil carbon modeling, which is crucial for voluntary carbon markets.

metadata.title: SAWGraph Spatial KG
metadata.description: The SAWGraph Spatial KG is part of the Safe Agricultural Products and Water Graph (SAWGraph) project. It contains all the Level 13 grid cells from the S2 grid as well as administrative regions of levels 1 to 3 (states, counties, and county subdivisions) and the spatial relationships between them for the 48 contiguous states in the U.S.

metadata.title: SPOKE GeneLab
metadata.description: The spoke-genelab KG complements the spokeokn (SPOKE Open Knowledge Network) KG and is designed to integrate omics data from NASAs Open Science Data Repository (OSDR/GeneLab), which hosts results from spaceflight experiments.

metadata.title: SPOKE-OKN
metadata.description: The spoke-okn (SPOKE Open Knowledge Network) KG is a comprehensive biomedical and environmental health knowledge graph that integrates diverse data across genomics, environmental science, and public health.

metadata.title: SUDOKN

single_graph.name: ubergraph_disease_hierarchy
single_graph.natural_language: Find all subtypes of infectious disease (MONDO:0005550)
single_graph.sparql:
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX MONDO: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/MONDO_>

SELECT DISTINCT ?disease ?label
WHERE {
  ?disease rdfs:subClassOf* MONDO:0005550 .
  ?disease rdfs:label ?label .
}
LIMIT 100
single_graph.notes: Uses transitive subClassOf (*) for hierarchy traversal in Ubergraph

single_graph.name: ubergraph_go_terms
single_graph.natural_language: Find GO biological process terms related to apoptosis
single_graph.sparql:
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX GO: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/GO_>

SELECT ?term ?label
WHERE {
  ?term rdfs:subClassOf* GO:0006915 .
  ?term rdfs:label ?label .
}
LIMIT 50
single_graph.notes: GO:0006915 is 'apoptotic process'. Returns child terms.

single_graph.name: ubergraph_phenotype_disease
single_graph.natural_language: Find diseases associated with fever phenotype
single_graph.sparql:
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX HP: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/HP_>
PREFIX obo: <http://purl.obolibrary.org/obo/>

SELECT DISTINCT ?disease ?diseaseLabel
WHERE {
  ?disease obo:RO_0002200 HP:0001945 .
  ?disease rdfs:label ?diseaseLabel .
}
LIMIT 50

single_graph.name: wikidata_human_genes
single_graph.natural_language: Find human genes associated with apoptosis GO term
single_graph.notes: P686=GO ID, P682=biological process, P703=found in taxon, P702=encoded by, Q15978631=Homo sapiens

single_graph.name: spoke_disease_prevalence
single_graph.natural_language: Find disease prevalence data by location
single_graph.sparql:
PREFIX neo4j: <neo4j://graph.schema#>
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>

SELECT ?disease ?diseaseLabel ?location
WHERE {
  ?disease a neo4j:Neo4jDisease .
  ?disease rdfs:label ?diseaseLabel .
  ?disease neo4j:PREVALENCE_DpL ?connection .
}
LIMIT 100
single_graph.notes: SPOKE uses Neo4j-derived schema. PREVALENCE_DpL = Disease prevalence in Location.

single_graph.name: aopwiki_pathways
single_graph.natural_language: Find adverse outcome pathways and their key events
single_graph.sparql:
PREFIX rdfs: <http://www.w3.org/2000/01/rdf-schema#>
PREFIX rdf: <http://www.w3.org/1999/02/22-rdf-syntax-ns#>

SELECT ?pathway ?pathwayLabel ?keyEvent ?eventLabel
WHERE {
  ?pathway rdf:type ?pathwayType .
  FILTER(CONTAINS(STR(?pathwayType), "AdverseOutcomePathway"))
  ?pathway rdfs:label ?pathwayLabel .
  ?pathway ?hasEvent ?keyEvent .
  FILTER(CONTAINS(STR(?hasEvent), "has_key_event"))
  OPTIONAL { ?keyEvent rdfs:label ?eventLabel . }
}
LIMIT 100
single_graph.notes: Queries AOP-Wiki for adverse outcome pathways and associated key events

ontology_and_data.description: Use ontology graphs for term resolution, then join with data graphs
ontology_and_data.join_strategy: IRI identity - same ontology term URI appears in both graphs

biomedical_ecosystem.description: Cross-query biomedical knowledge graphs for comprehensive data

wikidata_enrichment.description: Use Wikidata to enrich other graphs with identifiers and metadata
wikidata_enrichment.join_strategy: External ID properties in Wikidata (P5270=MONDO, P351=Entrez, etc.)

join_strategies.name: iri_identity
join_strategies.description: Join on identical IRIs across graphs (e.g., same MONDO disease URI)
join_strategies.example: ?disease in Ubergraph = ?disease in NDE (both use MONDO URIs)
join_strategies.sparql_pattern: # Same variable used in both SERVICE blocks

join_strategies.name: label_matching
join_strategies.description: Join on rdfs:label or schema:name text matching (less precise)

join_strategies.name: external_id_mapping
join_strategies.description: Use Wikidata external ID properties to link identifiers
join_strategies.example: Wikidata P5270 (MONDO ID) links to MONDO URIs in Ubergraph

usage_instructions.single_graph_query: For single-graph queries, use the sparql_endpoint URL directly. Include relevant prefixes from common_prefixes and the graph's specific prefixes. Check the graph's schema.classes and schema.properties to ensure valid predicates.
usage_instructions.federated_query: For federated queries across multiple graphs, use SERVICE clauses. The federated_endpoint (https://frink.apps.renci.org/?query=) can execute queries containing SERVICE clauses to multiple graph endpoints. Identify join points using shared IRIs or identifier mappings.
llm_prompt_hints: 1. Identify the domain: biomedical, ontology, geospatial, scholarly, etc.
2. Select appropriate graph(s) based on domain and data type needed
3. For ontology term lookups (disease, gene, phenotype, anatomy), start with ubergraph
4. For dataset/study discovery, use nde (NIAID Data Ecosystem)
5. For biomedical relationships (disease-compound, gene-disease), use spoke-okn
6. For identifier enrichment and cross-references, use wikidata
7. Include appropriate prefixes for the IRIs you're querying
9. For hierarchy traversal, use rdfs:subClassOf* (transitive closure)
10. Check example_queries for similar patterns to adapt
